import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

# Create a sample data frame
data = {'city': ['New York', 'Paris', 'Tokyo'],
        'population': [8500000, 2150000, 3500000],
        'GDP': [1700000000000, 600000000000, 550000000000]}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Plot the population against the GDP
plt.plot('population', 'GDP', data=df)
plt.xlabel('Population')
plt.ylabel('GDP')
plt.title('Comparing Population and GDP of Three Cities')
plt.show()
